# What NOT to send into the Docker build context (keeps the image small & safe).
# Like .gitignore, but it controls what `docker build` can see.

# Dependencies — always recompiled inside the image (better-sqlite3 is native:
# a Mac-built binary would not run on the Linux runtime).
node_modules

# Next.js build artifacts — rebuilt by the build stage.
.next
out

# Secrets & local runtime state — MUST NOT be baked into a shipped image.
.env
.env.local
data/app.db
data/app.db-wal
data/app.db-shm
# NOTE: data/enhanced-seed.db is intentionally NOT ignored — that committed seed
# template is copied into the image so first-run seeding works (see Dockerfile).

# Git, docs, and design reference — not needed at runtime.
.git
.gitignore
design-ref
*.md
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.log
